TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$x1 = random(5,8,1);
$y1 = random(2,7,1);
$m1 = random(2,5,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
The equation of the line with slope \($m1 \) that goes through the point
\( ( $x1 ,$y1 ) \) can be written in the form \( y = mx+b \) where
$PAR
 \( m = \)  \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $m1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
 \( b = \)  \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR
EOT

$ans = $y1 -$m1*$x1;
&ANS(std_num_cmp($ans));

